issue.title: Ideas
issue.body:
Selective content blocking
Rationale: Some domains contain both academic and distracting information. This should correctly determine the type of information such that it would block useless sites but allow for useful ones (idk why u would use reddit to do research in the first place)

If we want to use "AI" or "Machine Learning" then please do python
Word processing: [NLTK](https://www.nltk.org/) or [SpaCy](https://spacy.io/)
Training: Tensorflow

if it's just NLP and no ML then consider [node-nlp](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-nlp) and make this an extension or a script.
